What is the role of the web server
- the role of a web server is to show the static data on a website and make the transmission of http request with the client or the app server

What is the role of the application server
- do request validation
- the role is to take the request from the web server and treat it by sending an api request to the logic app file (business logic layer)
- when it receive a response from the logic app file it send the data back to the web server 

What is the role of the database
- the database is a vitrual storage that stock and organize data to be retrieve by the logic app file

What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website
- protocol more precisely hypertext transfer protocol

